<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="LootActions" i="action" m="interactions.utils.loot" n="loot_EP20World_FirewatchTower_NoteResponse" s="469373">
  <L n="loot_actions">
    <V t="notification_and_dialog">
      <U n="notification_and_dialog">
        <V n="dialog" t="notification">
          <U n="notification">
            <L n="dialog_options">
              <E>DISABLE_CLOSE_BUTTON</E>
            </L>
            <V n="icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="resource_key">
                <U n="resource_key">
                  <T n="key" p="InEP20\UI\Icons\Headlines\headline_PaperAirplane.png">2f7d0004:00000000:12137740cb2b0620</T>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0xDB2E345D<!--String: "Thank you kindly for your note. I'm doing fine up here, though I can't say the same about the weirdo who beefed it big time in their kayak over in the harbor. They looked around after like they were hoping no one saw, but I saw. I saw. "--></T>
                  <T>0x3C0D02F7<!--String: "Your note finds me in a fine stew, if I'm being honest. Some visitors have been over at the special boulder by the geyser just smacking it over and over again. I'm trying to concentrate on my puzzle—er—on my very important firewatch duties!"--></T>
                  <T>0xFCFE6287<!--String: "Thanks for dropping me a line. Gets lonely up here. I was looking through my binoculars and saw a bunch of bears having a big picnic in the woods, and I was wondering if I'm missing out just hangin' out in my tower all the time. But a job's a job, right?"--></T>
                  <T>0x4B0139BF<!--String: "I should write a better note in response to your last one, but if I'm being honest I've been distracted by watching Buddy Scoop trying to pawn off his latest crystal panning finds onto tourists all afternoon. That kid's got gumption, but I feel like he's one round of rock, paper, scissors away from big trouble if he doesn't check that attitude."--></T>
                  <T>0xE992AA48<!--String: "Hey, thanks for checking in with me. I'm doing just fine. I've been watching Sims show up for that Festival where they all dress up and exercise. I mean, you do you, but my clown costume only comes out on special occasions; I don't want to get sweat on it. "--></T>
                  <T>0xE75FC6E2<!--String: "Speaking of notes, I just saw a Sim head over to that Lonely Lighthouse in the harbor and put a note up on it. You know why they call it Lonely Lighthouse, right? Some Sims apparently don't like living solitary lives and will put up notes looking for friendship. I get the impulse, but frankly I'd rather just stay in my tower. Always nice to get a note from down below, though."--></T>
                  <T>0x6104B544<!--String: "As I was thinking about a response to write to your note, I found myself glancing over at that sunken plane in the harbor. Have you heard about that before? Apparently, some far-flung Landgraab managed to crash it because they were distracted by a plethora of Plumbirds gathered near the outcropping. Did you know that's the official word to use for a group of Plumbirds, by the way? A PLETHORA of Plumbirds. PLETHORA."--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
          </U>
        </V>
      </U>
    </V>
  </L>
</I>